<title>UK: United Friendly H1 pretax profit steady.</title>
<headline>United Friendly H1 pretax profit steady.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months ending June 30</p>
<p>				   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		41.4		   vs 44.0</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 11.2		   vs 7.3</p>
<p> Pretax		     50.6		   vs 50.2</p>
<p> Tax			  17.3		   vs 15.1</p>
<p> Net taxed		  33.3		   vs 35.1</p>
<p> Investment income	3.6		    vs 4.3</p>
<p> Pay date		   October 18</p>
<p>Div registration date  August 28 Note - United Friendly Plc has agreed a merger with Refuge Group Plc.</p>
<p>It said sales of single premium businesses, excluding SERPS, improved by 17 percent to 12 million stg while new ordinary branch annual premiums slipped to 9.4 million stg from 9.8 million stg.</p>
<p>New life and pensions annual premiums were up 19 percent to 1.9 million stg with single premiums, excluding SERPS, written through the financial planning business up 21 percent to 8.5 million stg.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717</p>
